<h4 id="toc16"><span>SCPs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-3533">SCP-3533</a> (&quot;<em>Metaphysiclean!</em>&quot;) - Conceptual recursion, applied vigorously by Billith.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3262">SCP-3262</a> (&quot;Fire of Unknown Origin&quot;) - Germinate. Detonate. Procreate. Grown by Communism will win.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2651">SCP-2651</a> (&quot;Gazing Upon a Failed Future&quot;) - &quot;<em>The not-god(?) lied here. Entrance is treason to the Koru-teusa and the Fourth World.</em>&quot; Written by 9Volt.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-1661">SCP-1661</a> (&quot;Gremlins&quot;) - Written by Shaggydredlocks.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3411">SCP-3411</a> (&quot;THE NEW YORK'S GLORIOUS CHILDREN'S BATALLION&quot;) - <em>REGRETTABLY THE WAR CONTINUES/THERE IS NO TIME FOR CHANGE</em> drafted by Tanhony.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3269">SCP-3269</a> (&quot;Pop Culture&quot;) - Ew. Exfoliated by Communism will win.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3254">SCP-3254</a> (&quot;Grant's Mama Bear&quot;) - Half robot. Half bear. All lover. Written by tretter.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3253">SCP-3253</a> (&quot;A Prison of Ink and Flesh&quot;) - The tattoo artist giveth, the tattoo artist taketh away. Written by Tzuvembi.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3528">SCP-3528</a> (&quot;Witch Hunter&quot;) - Nazis weren't known for a good batting average. Written by Weryllium.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3527">SCP-3527</a> (&quot;Incompetent Rap-Loving Bodysnatchers&quot;) - &quot;<em>Dumb bitch. I Tupac.</em>&quot; assumed by DrCaroll.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3273">SCP-3273</a> (&quot;Self-Performed Brain Editing Manual&quot;) - No pain, no gain. Written by Blibby_Blobfish.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3886">SCP-3886</a> (&quot;The Necromancer’s Saddle&quot;) -&quot;<em>I fear this is what Mr. Fuller had always intended.&quot;</em> Written by Ember16.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc17"><span>Tales</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/freaks-friends-and-fiends">Freaks, Friends and Fiends</a> - Iris Dark hunts a Nazi Goblin in a sewer, plus Lolly vents on why she hates the GOC so much. Written by DrChandra.</li>
<li><a href="/restless-dreams">Restless Dreams</a> - Oneiroi return in this addition to the War on All Fronts canon. Written by RecursiveRecursion.</li>
<li><a href="/one-trick-ponies">One Trick Ponies</a> - The story of the Foundation's most lovable good boy. Written by ratsy.</li>
<li><a href="/joey-fucknuts-builds-a-flying-machine">Joey Fucknuts Builds a Flying Machine</a> - The first of the SCP-3885 tale series. Written by CadaverCommander.</li>
<li><a href="/fire-and-brimstone">Fire and Brimstone</a> - Competitive Eschatology is back. Did you miss me? Written by Slothdude.</li>
<li><a href="/abject-blue-insomnia">Abject Blue Insomnia</a> - Dhole floated in nothingness. Conjured by Pedantique.</li>
<li><a href="/ash-and-maple-part-1">Ash and Maple ~ Part 1</a> - The GOC and The Serpent's Hand square off. Written by SifSeeker.</li>
<li><a href="/confiscated-documents-march-2022">Items Seized, March 2022, Site-42 Sapient Object Containment</a> - Take a glimpse into the minds and hearts of the Foundation's captives. Written by Cyantreuse.</li>
<li><a href="/worthashot">Worth a Shot</a> - &quot;THIS IS THE END, GOODBYE TO EVERYONE&quot; Exposited by ObserverSeptember.</li>
<li><a href="/jude-s-bizarre-adventure">Jude's Bizarre Adventure</a> - (or, The Doped-Up Sadboy Chronicles), Part V. Written by kinchtheknifeblade.</li>
<li><a href="/kit-always-used-to-think-she-was-cool">Kit Always Used to Think She Was Cool</a> - Apparently, Kit always used to think she was cool. Is she really? Written by Zachary Maxwell.</li>
<li><a class="newpage" href="/breaking-dawn">Breaking Dawn</a> - “As if anyone would want to do anything to you, David. You’re a freak.” Written by Zachary Maxwell.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc18"><span>GoI-Formats:</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/uiu-file-1988-021">UIU File: 1988-021</a> - [Unusual Incident Unit] &quot;<em>Case File &quot;Hy-Brasil Incident&quot;</em>&quot; Written by Baseplate-Actual.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc19"><span>Misc</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/jude-s-bizarre-adventure">Jude's Bizarre Adventure</a> - &quot;<em>Jude's Bizarre Adventure is about a jobless trans man who murders fourteen people and makes friends with a Jewish lesbian and a grandpa-loving twink, all the while trying to get revenge on a Critic for not being there when he was murdering people.</em>&quot; Written by kinchtheknifeblade.</li>
<li><a class="newpage" href="/document-2641-solidao">Document 2641-Solidão</a> - Written by FloppyPhoenix.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h4 id="toc20"><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<p>Folks over at the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scpdeclassified">SCPDeclassified</a> sub produced wonderful analysis of both <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/SCPDeclassified/comments/81n8cy/scp001_roget_keter_duty/">CODE NAME: Roget - Keter Duty</a> and <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/SCPDeclassified/comments/87i0iq/apotheosis_tale_seriesmtf_tau5_samsara/">Tau-5/Samsara</a>!!! <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/SCPDeclassified/">Check 'em out and subscibe!</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC8AmK8BHcHwu6bV_2Vdt0yg">Dr. Cimmerian</a> gives a rundown of Marshal, Carter, and Dark in <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vXBzJy_3-iA">Episode 10</a> of &quot;The Foundation&quot; podcast!</p>
<h4 id="toc21"><span>Fanart</span></h4>
<p>The wonderful Zhange has graced the winners of the 72-Hour Jamcon Contest with <a href="https://zhange-art.tumblr.com/post/172424576063/72-hour-jamcon-prizes">commissioned SCP artwork</a>!!! Bodacious!</p>
